      "term": "aciduric",
      "kind": "word",
      "cefrLevel": "C1",
      "senses": [
        {
          "pos": "adjective",
          "definition": "Able to live, grow, or remain active in a very acidic environment.",
          "examples": [
            "Aciduric bacteria can survive in the low pH of fruit juices.",[1][2][3][4]
            "Some aciduric microorganisms are important in food spoilage because they grow in acidic products like pickles and soft drinks.",[2][3][4][1]
            "Dentists study aciduric species of bacteria that can live in the acidic conditions created by sugar on teeth."[4]
          ],
          "collocations": [
            "aciduric bacteria",
